item.title: Field - r742snme
item.description: System name Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SNME Description System name

item.title: Field - r742snop
item.description: Number of no path conditions Zero for local entry. For outbound entry, count is for indicated transport class Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SNOP Description Number of no path conditions Zero for local entry. For outbound entry, count is for indicated transport class

item.title: Field - r742sout
item.description: Outbound Map: R742SYS Based on: r742sdir Description Outbound Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 1 of field r742sdir.

item.title: Field - r742sovr
item.description: Number of messages for which signalling service was optimized. Zero for inbound entry. Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SOVR Description Number of messages for which signalling service was optimized. Zero for inbound entry.

item.title: Field - r742spar
item.description: Partially not active during RMF post processor interval. Map: R742SYS Based on: r742sstf Description Partially not active during RMF post processor interval. Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 3 of field r742sstf.

item.title: Field - r742spth
item.description: Current number of paths in service. Zero for local entry. If outbound entry, count is for indicated transport class Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SPTH Description Current number of paths in service. Zero for local entry. If outbound entry, count is for indicated transport class

item.title: Field - r742sres
item.description: Counts reset by XCF during this interval Map: R742SYS Based on: r742sstf Description Counts reset by XCF during this interval Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 2 of field r742sstf.

item.title: Field - r742ssml
item.description: Number of messages too small conditions. Zero for inbound entry. Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SSML Description Number of messages too small conditions. Zero for inbound entry.

item.title: Field - r742sstf
item.description: Status flags Map: R742SYS Based on: R742SSTF Description Status flags Flag fields This is a flag field with the following bit fields: Field Bit-Position Description r742sact 0 System became active during this interval r742siac 1 System became inactive during this interval r742sres 2 Counts reset by XCF during this interval r742spar 3 Partially not active during RMF post processor interval.

item.title: Field - r742stcl
item.description: Message length for transport class. Zero for inbound entry. Map: R742SYS Based on: R742STCL Description Message length for transport class. Zero for inbound entry.

item.title: Field - r742stcn
item.description: Transport class name. Blanks for inbound entry. Map: R742SYS Based on: R742STCN Description Transport class name. Blanks for inbound entry.

item.title: Field - ral
item.description: Length of reassembly area. Area consists of a fixed header and a variable number of information blocks. Length depends on the record type/subtype, but is fixed for a specific type/subtype Map: SMF74PRO Based on: SMF74RAL Description Length of reassembly area. Area consists of a fixed header and a variable number of information blocks. Length depends on the record type/subtype, but is fixed for a specific type/subtype

item.title: Field - ran
item.description: Number of reassembly area. This field is used to indicate whether SMF record is broken. If 0, record is not broken. If 1, record is broken. Offset and length are only valid if SMFxxRAN is 1. Reassembly area is only present in broken records. Map: SMF74PRO Based on: SMF74RAN Description Number of reassembly area. This field is used to indicate whether SMF record is broken. If 0, record is not broken.

item.title: Field - rao
item.description: Offset to reassembly area relative to start of RMF product section Map: SMF74PRO Based on: SMF74RAO Description Offset to reassembly area relative to start of RMF product section

item.title: Field - rch
item.description: SMF record converted to higher release or service level. Bit is set by SMF record retrieval service GRBSMFR. Map: SMF74PRO Based on: fla Description SMF record converted to higher release or service level. Bit is set by SMF record retrieval service GRBSMFR. Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 5 of field fla.

item.title: Field - rcl
item.description: SMF record converted to lower service level. Bit is set by SMF record retrieval service GRBSMFR. Map: SMF74PRO Based on: fla Description SMF record converted to lower service level. Bit is set by SMF record retrieval service GRBSMFR. Post-Processed This virtual field corresponds to the flag at bit-position 4 of field fla.

item.description: Number of system data section Record: SMF74S2 Based on: SMF742SN Description Number of system data section
